1
00:02:05,166 --> 00:02:07,416
There are two
kinds of men, kuma.

2
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:08,958
Those who have
a sense of justice

3
00:02:09,041 --> 00:02:11,583
and those who just
create their own, kuma.

4
00:02:12,291 --> 00:02:13,666
[KYRIE] A coliseum?

5
00:02:13,750 --> 00:02:15,708
[MORTE] It's a place where
beastmen pay money to watch

6
00:02:15,791 --> 00:02:17,875
other beastmen attack
humans for sport.

7
00:02:17,958 --> 00:02:19,958
It's completely
senseless if you ask me.

8
00:02:20,041 --> 00:02:21,750
And for some reason
it's the most popular

9
00:02:21,833 --> 00:02:24,458
form of entertainment
around here.

10
00:02:24,541 --> 00:02:25,958
You don't want us
to put our fake ears on

11
00:02:26,041 --> 00:02:28,166
and head down to
watch this do you?

12
00:02:28,250 --> 00:02:29,833
[MORTE] Of course not, idiot...

13
00:02:29,916 --> 00:02:33,291
The smartest move we could make
is to avoid that town entirely.

14
00:02:33,375 --> 00:02:35,375
I heard that when they run out
of fighters from their prison,

15
00:02:35,458 --> 00:02:37,416
thugs from the
coliseum kidnap any humans

16
00:02:37,500 --> 00:02:40,333
they can find to fight
in the remaining battles.

17
00:02:44,375 --> 00:02:45,916
What's wrong?

18
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,500
Nothing, I just heard
something and thought

19
00:02:47,583 --> 00:02:49,916
it might have been
those thugs coming for us.

20
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,083
[KYRIE] Huh?!

21
00:02:51,166 --> 00:02:53,250
Come on out you thugs!

22
00:02:54,125 --> 00:02:59,166
[footsteps]

23
00:02:59,250 --> 00:03:00,458
It's just Toppy!

24
00:03:00,541 --> 00:03:01,833
I knew you were just
trying to scare me

25
00:03:01,916 --> 00:03:03,500
[KYRIE] with that stupid story.

26
00:03:03,583 --> 00:03:04,791
So where are all the fish?

27
00:03:04,875 --> 00:03:05,750
Looks like you--

28
00:03:05,833 --> 00:03:07,333
[gasp]

29
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,458
[gasp]

30
00:03:14,541 --> 00:03:24,541
♪

31
00:03:33,291 --> 00:03:38,541
[cheering and yelling]

32
00:03:38,625 --> 00:03:40,750
[MOLE] Make him feel the pain!

33
00:03:40,833 --> 00:03:42,291
[MOUSE] Woo hoo!

34
00:03:44,083 --> 00:03:45,458
[crowd cheers]

35
00:04:03,958 --> 00:04:06,000
Wait, your story...
It was true!

36
00:04:06,083 --> 00:04:07,916
It seems we've
been kidnapped.

37
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:09,125
But how did we
get ourselves trapped

38
00:04:09,208 --> 00:04:11,291
inside the coliseum?!

39
00:04:11,375 --> 00:04:13,958
That little bear
and his thugs got us.

40
00:04:14,041 --> 00:04:16,333
I couldn't take all of them.

41
00:04:16,416 --> 00:04:17,625
So it was
another little bear

42
00:04:17,708 --> 00:04:19,416
and not Toppy
that kidnapped us?

43
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:21,958
Wait, didn't you say
humans battle beastmen here?

44
00:04:22,041 --> 00:04:23,166
[distant cheering]

45
00:04:23,250 --> 00:04:24,250
[ANNOUNCER] And now
the moment that you've

46
00:04:24,333 --> 00:04:25,666
all been waiting for.

47
00:04:25,750 --> 00:04:28,166
Striking fear into the
hearts of all who face him...

48
00:04:28,250 --> 00:04:31,458
give it up for our horse
warrior from the planet Dart!

49
00:04:31,541 --> 00:04:35,833
[cheering]

50
00:04:35,916 --> 00:04:37,291
[neigh]

51
00:04:43,541 --> 00:04:44,500
[MORTE] Hey, Kyrie.

52
00:04:44,583 --> 00:04:45,958
Huh?

53
00:04:47,083 --> 00:04:48,208
You should
put that on.

54
00:04:48,291 --> 00:04:50,625
It might help you
more than the last guy.

55
00:04:50,708 --> 00:04:52,416
[KYRIE worried wimper]

56
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,250
[KYRIE] Ahh-huh.

57
00:04:57,833 --> 00:04:58,833
Hey, settle down.

58
00:04:58,916 --> 00:05:00,000
You're up next, so
give the customers

59
00:05:00,083 --> 00:05:01,750
a good show 
before you die.

60
00:05:01,833 --> 00:05:03,708
Wait we're going
out to fight?

61
00:05:03,791 --> 00:05:05,375
Well whadya think
you were gonna do here.

62
00:05:05,458 --> 00:05:07,791
Just don't spoil the
fans fun by dying to soon.

63
00:05:07,875 --> 00:05:09,666
I hate it when that happens.

64
00:05:09,750 --> 00:05:12,208
'Kay. Good to know...
We'll... try our best...

65
00:05:13,166 --> 00:05:14,458
Oh, Morte!

66
00:05:14,541 --> 00:05:16,291
[MORTE] Will you calm down?!

67
00:05:16,375 --> 00:05:19,583
Weren't you listening?
It's just a horse warrior.

68
00:05:19,666 --> 00:05:22,500
We'll fight our
way right outta here.

69
00:05:22,583 --> 00:05:24,458
Listen to yourself.
How can you be so calm?

70
00:05:24,541 --> 00:05:26,458
It's a horse warrior...

71
00:05:26,541 --> 00:05:28,083
Toppy, please come back!

72
00:05:28,166 --> 00:05:30,666
We could really use
your help right about now.

73
00:05:32,166 --> 00:05:34,875
[MAN] Listen mate...
two humans traveling together?

74
00:05:34,958 --> 00:05:38,500
That's not such an uncommon
sight 'round these parts.

75
00:05:41,666 --> 00:05:44,000
Can't say I've
seen those two.

76
00:05:44,083 --> 00:05:46,541
Alright. Thanks
anyway, kuma.

77
00:05:47,125 --> 00:05:50,541
[distant wincing]

78
00:05:50,625 --> 00:05:51,958
No!

79
00:05:52,041 --> 00:05:54,500
A fluffy piece of tail
like you needs a real man.

80
00:05:54,583 --> 00:05:56,083
[wincing]

81
00:05:56,166 --> 00:05:57,833
[chuckle]

82
00:05:57,916 --> 00:05:59,333
Stop it!

83
00:05:59,833 --> 00:06:01,500
[TOPPY] Let go
of her now, kuma!

84
00:06:02,375 --> 00:06:03,750
What?!

85
00:06:03,833 --> 00:06:05,916
Did you say that?

86
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,500
[TOPPY] Down here, kuma.

87
00:06:11,375 --> 00:06:13,875
Did you not
hear the lady, kuma?

88
00:06:13,958 --> 00:06:16,625
Aww, look at the bear?

89
00:06:16,708 --> 00:06:18,458
Ahhh!

90
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:23,625
Don't worry, miss. You'll
be alright now, kuma.

91
00:06:23,708 --> 00:06:27,083
Oh, how can I ever repay
you for your kindness?

92
00:06:27,166 --> 00:06:30,375
[MAN] You don't seem to
have changed one bit, bear.

93
00:06:37,791 --> 00:06:39,916
[TOPPY] Yappy...?

94
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:50,000
[crowd cheering]

95
00:06:52,708 --> 00:06:55,166
[HORSE] Ugh...

96
00:06:55,250 --> 00:06:57,833
[cheering]

97
00:06:57,916 --> 00:06:59,708
What an upset to for
the warriors from Dart!

98
00:06:59,791 --> 00:07:02,333
A top fighter taken out!
In their coliseum debut

99
00:07:02,416 --> 00:07:04,041
these fresh meat
humans have displayed

100
00:07:04,125 --> 00:07:05,250
[ANNOUNCER] that they
are here to fight...

101
00:07:05,333 --> 00:07:06,833
Is it over?

102
00:07:08,958 --> 00:07:10,625
It's over.

103
00:07:13,208 --> 00:07:14,583
Well, bear...

104
00:07:14,666 --> 00:07:17,666
When was the last time
we saw each other, bear?

105
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:20,166
[TOPPY] Been about
twenty years since we

106
00:07:20,250 --> 00:07:22,250
left our village
together, kuma...

107
00:07:22,333 --> 00:07:24,375
Has time treated
you well, kuma?

108
00:07:24,458 --> 00:07:26,416
[YAPPY] As well as
can be expected, bear.

109
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:28,166
How about you, bear?

110
00:07:28,250 --> 00:07:30,625
[TOPPY] It's actually been
a little rough, lately, kuma.

111
00:07:30,708 --> 00:07:34,125
[BAR OWNER] Here you go
fellas. One jumbo salmon.

112
00:07:34,208 --> 00:07:35,875
Courtesy of the
woman over there.

113
00:07:35,958 --> 00:07:45,208
♪

114
00:07:45,291 --> 00:07:46,583
Rock!

115
00:07:46,666 --> 00:07:47,708
Paper!

116
00:07:47,791 --> 00:07:49,166
[TOPPY] Kuma!
[YAPPY] Bear!

117
00:07:50,458 --> 00:07:52,083
[TOPPY chuckles]
[YAPPY grunts]

118
00:07:52,166 --> 00:07:53,958
[TOPPY] Just Like
old times, kuma.

119
00:07:56,583 --> 00:07:58,458
[YAPPY] Yeah, just
like old times when you

120
00:07:58,541 --> 00:08:01,083
always win and things
go your way, bear.

121
00:08:01,166 --> 00:08:03,291
[TOPPY] You always
pick rock, kuma.

122
00:08:03,375 --> 00:08:06,250
You know that girl reminded
me of that one time...

123
00:08:07,708 --> 00:08:11,875
[DOGS chuckling]

124
00:08:11,958 --> 00:08:13,416
[TOPPY] That day when
you and I first pledged

125
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:15,375
to become heroes, kuma.

126
00:08:15,458 --> 00:08:17,250
[YAPPY] Well that was
an entire lifetime ago

127
00:08:17,333 --> 00:08:19,958
but what brings you all
the way out here, bear?

128
00:08:20,041 --> 00:08:22,083
Some companions of mine
I've been traveling with

129
00:08:22,166 --> 00:08:23,625
went missing and I
fear that they've gone

130
00:08:23,708 --> 00:08:25,791
and gotten themselves
captured, kuma.

131
00:08:26,625 --> 00:08:28,500
[YAPPY] Captured? Wait...

132
00:08:28,583 --> 00:08:31,000
Do you have human
companions, bear?

133
00:08:31,083 --> 00:08:32,583
[TOPPY] Yep, kuma.

134
00:08:32,666 --> 00:08:35,375
[YAPPY] Why would you be
traveling with humans, bear?

135
00:08:35,458 --> 00:08:37,583
It's kind of a
long story, kuma.

136
00:08:37,666 --> 00:08:39,458
Besides it's not like
either one of us could ever

137
00:08:39,541 --> 00:08:42,458
turn our backs on a person
who's in trouble, kuma.

138
00:08:42,541 --> 00:08:44,333
You haven't seen them, have you?

139
00:08:44,416 --> 00:08:45,666
A short-tempered brunette girl

140
00:08:45,750 --> 00:08:48,458
and a completely
passive blonde guy, kuma.

141
00:08:50,375 --> 00:08:51,625
No.

142
00:08:51,708 --> 00:08:56,916
[distant cheering]

143
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:58,666
It seems that a
human's been winning.

144
00:08:58,750 --> 00:09:00,125
It's rare that a
human even makes it

145
00:09:00,208 --> 00:09:02,375
past the first round anymore.

146
00:09:02,458 --> 00:09:03,708
[TOPPY] A human?

147
00:09:03,791 --> 00:09:05,166
Yeah. Reports've been
sayin' that an incredibly

148
00:09:05,250 --> 00:09:07,000
strong girl is
taking warriors down

149
00:09:07,083 --> 00:09:10,000
single-handedly while
her male partner just hides.

150
00:09:10,791 --> 00:09:11,708
Sounds like...

151
00:09:11,791 --> 00:09:13,166
[THUG A] Hey, Yappy!

152
00:09:16,583 --> 00:09:18,125
Old friend...
it seems I have some

153
00:09:18,208 --> 00:09:20,250
business to attend to, bear.

154
00:09:23,583 --> 00:09:25,500
Excuse me barkeep, but do
you know what will happen

155
00:09:25,583 --> 00:09:28,541
to those humans after they've
won their battle, kuma?

156
00:09:28,625 --> 00:09:30,375
I'm not sure, but
since the coliseum

157
00:09:30,458 --> 00:09:32,041
doubles as a prison,
as long as they're

158
00:09:32,125 --> 00:09:34,000
not killed in battle,
they'll most likely

159
00:09:34,083 --> 00:09:36,791
[BAR OWNER] be back
to rot in their cells.

160
00:09:38,791 --> 00:09:40,500
Yappy you've really
outdone yourself this time

161
00:09:40,583 --> 00:09:41,875
with such a great find!

162
00:09:41,958 --> 00:09:43,958
Those two humans are
winning all of their matches.

163
00:09:44,041 --> 00:09:46,208
Not only are the
fights exciting...

164
00:09:46,291 --> 00:09:47,791
but look!

165
00:09:47,875 --> 00:09:49,750
[ANNOUNCER] See all the profits
we've made off of them!

166
00:09:49,833 --> 00:09:52,083
Isn't this more rewarding
than that hero junk

167
00:09:52,166 --> 00:09:53,875
you used to go on about?

168
00:09:54,958 --> 00:09:57,208
[ANNOUNCER] Look... Heroes
save peoples' lives while

169
00:09:57,291 --> 00:09:59,333
you kidnap them and since
you've crossed that line,

170
00:09:59,416 --> 00:10:01,208
you can never go back.

171
00:10:01,291 --> 00:10:03,750
Take all of this money
down and put it in the safe.

172
00:10:03,833 --> 00:10:05,208
[THUG A] Yes, sir!

173
00:10:14,291 --> 00:10:16,041
[GUARD] Hey! You're
not allowed down here--

174
00:10:22,125 --> 00:10:23,500
Aughhh...

175
00:10:23,583 --> 00:10:25,125
[footsteps]

176
00:10:25,208 --> 00:10:27,208
Sorry I'm late, kuma.

177
00:10:27,291 --> 00:10:28,916
Toppy!

178
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:30,750
Is it really you?

179
00:10:49,208 --> 00:10:50,666
Hmph.

180
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:53,083
A little bear that
looked just like me, kuma?

181
00:10:53,166 --> 00:10:55,791
Yeah. And at first I
thought it was you.

182
00:10:55,875 --> 00:10:57,166
No way...

183
00:10:57,250 --> 00:10:59,541
It can't be him, kuma.

184
00:11:00,583 --> 00:11:01,958
[TOPPY and YAPPY] Ugh!

185
00:11:02,041 --> 00:11:03,708
Uh...

186
00:11:03,791 --> 00:11:04,916
[BOTH gasp]

187
00:11:06,583 --> 00:11:08,958
[distant footsteps]

188
00:11:09,041 --> 00:11:10,541
[GUARD] Hey, did
you guys hear that?

189
00:11:12,833 --> 00:11:14,208
[YAPPY] Down this way, bear!

190
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,625
These humans here are
trying to escape, bear!

191
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:21,208
Apprehend them, bear!

192
00:11:22,208 --> 00:11:23,708
Wait, I don't get it, kuma.

193
00:11:23,791 --> 00:11:26,541
Imprison that beastman
while you're at it, bear.

194
00:11:26,625 --> 00:11:28,583
He's the one who
let them out, bear!

195
00:11:28,666 --> 00:11:29,791
Yappy, why?!

196
00:11:29,875 --> 00:11:31,375
[KYRIE] Ugh--
[MORTE] Kyrie!

197
00:11:32,500 --> 00:11:33,875
[TOPPY] Augh!

198
00:11:37,625 --> 00:11:39,583
Old friend...

199
00:11:53,666 --> 00:11:55,000
[ANNOUNCER] You want
that other little bear

200
00:11:55,083 --> 00:11:56,625
to fight with the humans?

201
00:11:56,708 --> 00:11:58,916
Do you honestly think
our patrons will wanna see

202
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:00,708
a beastman fighting
alongside them?

203
00:12:00,791 --> 00:12:03,083
[YAPPY] I think your customers
will appreciate a battle that's

204
00:12:03,166 --> 00:12:05,750
unlike anything
they've ever seen, bear.

205
00:12:05,833 --> 00:12:08,125
You make a good argument.
Besides I hired you

206
00:12:08,208 --> 00:12:10,041
to find me the
fresh meat...

207
00:12:10,125 --> 00:12:11,708
So what's the backstory?

208
00:12:11,791 --> 00:12:14,750
Why exactly are you sending this
friend of yours into battle?

209
00:12:14,833 --> 00:12:16,416
He's no
friend of mine.

210
00:12:16,500 --> 00:12:17,958
He's an excellent
fighter that bookies

211
00:12:18,041 --> 00:12:20,541
will completely
underestimate, bear.

212
00:12:20,625 --> 00:12:23,333
[ANNOUNCER] Allowing us
to pocket a small fortune...

213
00:12:23,416 --> 00:12:25,166
I have just one other question.

214
00:12:25,250 --> 00:12:26,625
I'm glad you
prevented their escape,

215
00:12:26,708 --> 00:12:29,500
but what exactly were
you doing down there?

216
00:12:29,583 --> 00:12:32,541
My whereabouts isn't
any of your business, bear.

217
00:12:34,291 --> 00:12:35,791
Hm...

218
00:12:35,875 --> 00:12:37,708
[THUG A] You heard right
folks! For the first time ever

219
00:12:37,791 --> 00:12:39,666
humans and a beastman
fighting together!

220
00:12:39,750 --> 00:12:42,708
Odds are fifty to one. Step
on up and place your bets!

221
00:12:42,791 --> 00:12:44,333
But with the three of
us fighting together,

222
00:12:44,416 --> 00:12:45,625
isn't someone
gonna notice we're

223
00:12:45,708 --> 00:12:47,375
the World
Destruction Committee?

224
00:12:47,458 --> 00:12:48,916
That's what
you're worried about?

225
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:50,666
Well if someone does
notice, we won't only

226
00:12:50,750 --> 00:12:53,000
have to defeat a warrior
but an entire coliseum

227
00:12:53,083 --> 00:12:55,458
full of greedy beastmen.

228
00:12:55,541 --> 00:12:58,041
[TOPPY] I still
don't understand, kuma...

229
00:12:59,125 --> 00:13:00,333
Yappy...

230
00:13:00,416 --> 00:13:02,000
[MORTE] What's to understand?

231
00:13:02,083 --> 00:13:03,416
Your old friend wants to kill us

232
00:13:03,500 --> 00:13:05,375
and he's found a
nice legal way to do it.

233
00:13:05,458 --> 00:13:07,625
[TOPPY] You don't know Yappy!
He's a hero... He'd never...

234
00:13:07,708 --> 00:13:09,333
How can you continue to
just sit there and defend him

235
00:13:09,416 --> 00:13:11,458
like this when he's
the one that turned us in?

236
00:13:11,541 --> 00:13:12,875
You saw with your
own eyes that he was

237
00:13:12,958 --> 00:13:14,250
stealing that bag
of money until he

238
00:13:14,333 --> 00:13:16,250
sold out a friend
to save his own tail.

239
00:13:16,333 --> 00:13:17,500
If that's your
idea of a hero,

240
00:13:17,583 --> 00:13:19,666
you really do belong
on a wanted poster.

241
00:13:19,750 --> 00:13:21,500
Why are you being
so mean, Morte?

242
00:13:21,583 --> 00:13:23,583
It's the truth! Toppy
is free to continue

243
00:13:23,666 --> 00:13:25,625
deluding himself into
believing that the one who

244
00:13:25,708 --> 00:13:27,416
[MORTE] ambushed us
with his band of thugs

245
00:13:27,500 --> 00:13:29,833
and had us locked up here
is still an "old friend."

246
00:13:29,916 --> 00:13:31,291
Who am I to stop him?

247
00:13:31,375 --> 00:13:33,208
But I refuse
to listen to it!

248
00:13:33,291 --> 00:13:34,375
[footsteps]

249
00:13:34,458 --> 00:13:36,416
[GUARD A] Hey, you
three! You're up next!

250
00:13:37,791 --> 00:13:39,416
Hrm...

251
00:13:39,833 --> 00:13:44,791
[cheering]

252
00:13:44,875 --> 00:13:47,000
Yappy... Are you sure
this is the opponent

253
00:13:47,083 --> 00:13:48,333
we should be
starting with?

254
00:13:48,416 --> 00:13:49,833
We won't make any
real money if these three

255
00:13:49,916 --> 00:13:52,083
can't make it past
the initial battle.

256
00:13:52,166 --> 00:13:54,166
Oh, I'm most
certain, bear.

257
00:13:54,250 --> 00:13:56,000
Yeah, take 'em all out, girlie!

258
00:13:56,083 --> 00:13:58,375
[SPECTATOR] Do something
besides cry this time, you wimp!

259
00:13:58,458 --> 00:13:59,750
[ANNOUNCER] Ladies
and gentleman!

260
00:13:59,833 --> 00:14:01,708
I present to you
a monumental battle

261
00:14:01,791 --> 00:14:04,500
unlike anything you've ever
witnessed in your lives.

262
00:14:04,583 --> 00:14:06,125
Fresh from their
unexpected winning streak,

263
00:14:06,208 --> 00:14:08,375
the two human challengers
are joined by a beastman

264
00:14:08,458 --> 00:14:12,083
to form... The
Gladiator Dream Team!

265
00:14:12,166 --> 00:14:13,916
Let's see how long
they last facing the

266
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:16,125
warrior-devouring Sand Worm!

267
00:14:16,208 --> 00:14:18,375
Sand Worm?! Where at?

268
00:14:20,583 --> 00:14:21,958
[ALL] Ahhh!

269
00:14:22,583 --> 00:14:24,250
[SAND WORM growl]

270
00:14:28,541 --> 00:14:29,916
[coughing]

271
00:14:31,708 --> 00:14:33,500
[panicking]

272
00:14:40,833 --> 00:14:42,416
[gasp and heavy breathing]

273
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:45,583
Wow! And the Sand Worm's
assault just keeps coming!

274
00:14:47,791 --> 00:14:49,166
[TOPPY] Uh!

275
00:14:53,958 --> 00:14:55,458
[ANNOUNCER gasps]
[YAPPY] Hmph.

276
00:15:00,291 --> 00:15:01,666
Hyaaah!

277
00:15:03,916 --> 00:15:06,750
[SAND WORM growls]

278
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:11,166
Incredible!
What an upset...!

279
00:15:11,250 --> 00:15:14,583
[ANNOUNCER] Our challengers come
from behind to take the win!

280
00:15:14,916 --> 00:15:16,541
Hm, hm, hm, hm.

281
00:15:16,625 --> 00:15:17,666
Toppy!

282
00:15:17,750 --> 00:15:19,958
You saved us, Toppy!

283
00:15:20,041 --> 00:15:21,416
[MORTE and KYRIE] Huh?

284
00:15:29,083 --> 00:15:31,833
[ANNOUNCER] Do you think our
dream team is warmed up yet?

285
00:15:31,916 --> 00:15:34,916
Up next in our battle series,
a warrior who has taken out

286
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,791
countless gladiators
with his death swing!

287
00:15:37,875 --> 00:15:40,125
It's the Minotaur Holstein!

288
00:15:40,208 --> 00:15:42,208
Wait! We're stuck
in a battle series?!

289
00:15:42,291 --> 00:15:43,708
Yappy, how far will you go to

290
00:15:43,791 --> 00:15:45,166
ensure that we're dead, kuma?

291
00:15:45,250 --> 00:15:46,541
He's coming!

292
00:15:46,625 --> 00:15:48,000
[bellows]

293
00:15:48,625 --> 00:15:50,791
[screaming] I-I don't wanna die!

294
00:15:50,875 --> 00:15:52,333
[grunting]

295
00:15:52,416 --> 00:15:54,375
[screaming]

296
00:15:54,458 --> 00:15:55,833
[KYRIE] Ugh!

297
00:15:57,041 --> 00:15:58,750
[MINOTAUR HOLSTEIN grunts]

298
00:15:58,833 --> 00:16:04,250
[TOPPY struggling]

299
00:16:04,333 --> 00:16:05,458
Toppy!

300
00:16:05,541 --> 00:16:09,666
[MINOTAUR HOLSTEIN
and TOPPY struggling]

301
00:16:09,750 --> 00:16:15,208
♪

302
00:16:15,291 --> 00:16:17,208
[YAPPY chuckles]

303
00:16:17,291 --> 00:16:24,750
♪

304
00:16:24,833 --> 00:16:28,458
Do you remember
me from yesterday?

305
00:16:28,541 --> 00:16:30,541
That little bear's
the one who saved me.

306
00:16:30,625 --> 00:16:32,041
Leave me alone, bear.

307
00:16:32,125 --> 00:16:34,125
Uh. What do you mean?

308
00:16:34,208 --> 00:16:36,250
[WOMAN] Aren't you
going to help him?

309
00:16:36,916 --> 00:16:40,041
[MINOTAUR HOLSTEIN
and TOPPY struggling]

310
00:16:40,125 --> 00:16:42,708
How can you walk away
and not help your friend?

311
00:16:42,791 --> 00:16:44,583
[TOPPY] Kuma...!

312
00:16:45,083 --> 00:16:48,166
I'm begging you, sir. Please,
you just have to save him.

313
00:16:49,083 --> 00:16:50,458
Why should I?

314
00:16:50,541 --> 00:16:51,541
Huh?

315
00:16:51,625 --> 00:16:52,958
What makes that
little bear so much

316
00:16:53,041 --> 00:16:55,250
more special
than me, bear?

317
00:16:55,333 --> 00:16:57,583
[YAPPY] The truth is, before he
stepped in and saved the day,

318
00:16:57,666 --> 00:17:00,125
I had planned on
being your hero.

319
00:17:00,208 --> 00:17:02,250
He's not the
only hero, bear!

320
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:03,583
[gasps]

321
00:17:03,666 --> 00:17:07,166
So why save him?
Tell me that, bear.

322
00:17:07,250 --> 00:17:08,583
[cheering]

323
00:17:08,666 --> 00:17:10,208
Dumb cow!

324
00:17:10,708 --> 00:17:12,083
Try this!

325
00:17:15,833 --> 00:17:17,291
[TOPPY] Mmm-ughhh!

326
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:22,458
[crowd cheering]

327
00:17:22,541 --> 00:17:24,750
[YAPPY] Toppy...

328
00:17:24,833 --> 00:17:26,833
Why is it always you, bear?

329
00:17:31,416 --> 00:17:32,875
Are you two okay, kuma?

330
00:17:32,958 --> 00:17:34,166
Yeah, we're fine.
How are you feeling

331
00:17:34,250 --> 00:17:36,000
after taking on
that minotaur?

332
00:17:36,083 --> 00:17:38,750
There's no need to
worry about me, kuma.

333
00:17:49,958 --> 00:17:52,625
What?! Has he lost his mind?!

334
00:17:53,458 --> 00:17:55,083
On the other hand...

335
00:17:55,166 --> 00:17:58,250
this is too good an
opportunity to pass up!

336
00:17:58,333 --> 00:18:01,166
Hey! Go gather up the
bets and bring them to me.

337
00:18:02,583 --> 00:18:04,416
[ANNOUNCER] If you thought
that was all we had,

338
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:06,583
you're in for a real treat!

339
00:18:06,666 --> 00:18:08,666
Now for your viewing pleasure...

340
00:18:08,750 --> 00:18:10,666
a hate-fueled grudge match

341
00:18:10,750 --> 00:18:14,958
between two fellow baby bears!

342
00:18:15,708 --> 00:18:18,583
So you've decided to
try and kill us yourself?

343
00:18:18,666 --> 00:18:20,833
Just tell me
one thing, Yappy.

344
00:18:20,916 --> 00:18:23,250
When we vowed to become
heroes who stood for justice,

345
00:18:23,333 --> 00:18:26,125
were you lying to me
or just yourself, kuma?!

346
00:18:29,166 --> 00:18:30,875
Yappy!

347
00:18:32,375 --> 00:18:33,750
It's my fight, kuma!

348
00:18:33,833 --> 00:18:35,333
[grunting]

349
00:18:35,416 --> 00:18:37,541
[running breaths]

350
00:18:37,625 --> 00:18:47,583
♪

351
00:18:57,833 --> 00:18:59,833
While I was trying to
be a hero as good as you,

352
00:18:59,916 --> 00:19:02,041
I accidentally
killed someone, bear.

353
00:19:02,708 --> 00:19:03,958
[YAPPY] How could
I go on being a hero

354
00:19:04,041 --> 00:19:06,041
after what I had done, bear?

355
00:19:06,125 --> 00:19:08,916
That bird took me in, so
this is my life now, bear!

356
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:11,250
That's your excuse
for becoming a kidnapper?

357
00:19:11,333 --> 00:19:13,125
Don't make me laugh, kuma.

358
00:19:16,708 --> 00:19:18,125
[YAPPY grunts]

359
00:19:21,041 --> 00:19:22,666
You don't know
how hard it's been.

360
00:19:22,750 --> 00:19:24,250
Things don't
just come to me...

361
00:19:24,333 --> 00:19:26,541
You have no right
to judge my life!

362
00:19:26,625 --> 00:19:27,916
[YAPPY] Bear!

363
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,375
[TOPPY] Kuma!

364
00:19:37,458 --> 00:19:38,916
Huuuh...

365
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:40,875
Uggghhh!

366
00:19:44,833 --> 00:19:46,291
[TOPPY] Kuma.

367
00:19:48,083 --> 00:19:50,666
[cheering]

368
00:19:50,750 --> 00:19:53,333
What a fight! And
there you have it folks!

369
00:19:53,416 --> 00:19:56,541
A swift punch and
the bear goes down!

370
00:19:58,583 --> 00:20:02,000
[laughing] So much profit...

371
00:20:09,375 --> 00:20:11,750
Yappy...
heroes make mistakes

372
00:20:11,833 --> 00:20:13,875
but how'd it
get this far, kuma?

373
00:20:14,625 --> 00:20:17,458
[grunts]

374
00:20:17,541 --> 00:20:19,333
I'm no hero!

375
00:20:19,416 --> 00:20:21,458
[THUG B] Boss,
something's wrong!

376
00:20:22,958 --> 00:20:24,208
What now?

377
00:20:24,291 --> 00:20:26,791
It's disappeared! All the
money in the safe is gone!

378
00:20:26,875 --> 00:20:28,125
What?!

379
00:20:28,208 --> 00:20:31,208
Money just doesn't
disappear, so where'd it go?!

380
00:20:31,291 --> 00:20:32,916
I-I'm not certain.

381
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:34,208
Actually boss...

382
00:20:34,291 --> 00:20:35,750
Tell me!

383
00:20:36,750 --> 00:20:38,666
[THUG A] The night when the
prisoners tried to escape,

384
00:20:38,750 --> 00:20:41,291
I saw someone's shadow
near where the safe is kept.

385
00:20:41,375 --> 00:20:42,750
[ANNOUNCER] Who's was it?!

386
00:20:43,791 --> 00:20:45,833
[THUG A] Well, the person's
shadow looked like it

387
00:20:45,916 --> 00:20:48,083
could've been
from a little bear...

388
00:20:48,166 --> 00:20:50,041
But when could a little bear...

389
00:20:50,125 --> 00:20:51,583
[squaks]

390
00:20:51,666 --> 00:20:53,208
[ANNOUNCER] I'm glad you
prevented their escape,

391
00:20:53,291 --> 00:20:56,333
but what exactly were
you doing down there.

392
00:20:56,416 --> 00:20:59,375
My whereabouts isn't
any of your business, bear.

393
00:21:00,458 --> 00:21:02,666
He wouldn't dare...

394
00:21:05,666 --> 00:21:09,000
[laughing and cheering]

395
00:21:09,083 --> 00:21:11,625
[YAPPY] I can never
again be a hero.

396
00:21:12,666 --> 00:21:14,916
[YAPPY] A murderer...
A kidnapper... A thief...

397
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:16,083
Those are what I've become

398
00:21:16,166 --> 00:21:18,791
and I will accept
the consequences, bear!

399
00:21:19,541 --> 00:21:20,500
The thief is--

400
00:21:20,583 --> 00:21:22,583
[TOPPY] It was me, kuma!

401
00:21:24,708 --> 00:21:25,875
[squaks]

402
00:21:25,958 --> 00:21:27,583
[TOPPY] You have no idea
who you've messed with,

403
00:21:27,666 --> 00:21:28,791
do you, kuma?

404
00:21:28,875 --> 00:21:30,208
I'm the dreaded
Toppy of the World

405
00:21:30,291 --> 00:21:31,750
Destruction Committee, kuma!

406
00:21:31,833 --> 00:21:33,750
Shut your fat mouth!

407
00:21:33,833 --> 00:21:37,166
And I've already taken all your
beloved gambling money, kuma!

408
00:21:37,250 --> 00:21:38,958
The Toppy?

409
00:21:39,041 --> 00:21:41,041
Wait, those three
down there...

410
00:21:41,125 --> 00:21:43,250
[OX SPECTATOR] are the
World Destruction Committee?

411
00:21:43,333 --> 00:21:44,791
[WOLF SPECTATOR] The ones
from the wanted posters

412
00:21:44,875 --> 00:21:46,375
with the huge reward...

413
00:21:46,458 --> 00:21:47,625
Reward?

414
00:21:47,708 --> 00:21:48,875
Reward!

415
00:21:48,958 --> 00:21:50,833
[OX SPECTATOR] Oh yeah!
We're gonna be rich!

416
00:21:52,833 --> 00:21:54,166
What the--?

417
00:21:54,250 --> 00:21:55,583
[CAT SPECTATOR] Go for the
bird! He's got our money!

418
00:21:55,666 --> 00:21:57,041
Help me!

419
00:21:57,125 --> 00:22:00,208
World Destruction...
Why would you--?

420
00:22:00,291 --> 00:22:03,791
Yappy, no matter what
life throws at you,

421
00:22:03,875 --> 00:22:05,500
you'll always be a
hero by standing up

422
00:22:05,583 --> 00:22:07,333
for what you
know is right, kuma.

423
00:22:07,416 --> 00:22:09,125
We have to leave
right now, Toppy!

424
00:22:09,208 --> 00:22:10,875
Come on!

425
00:22:10,958 --> 00:22:13,000
I'll always fight
to be a hero...

426
00:22:13,083 --> 00:22:15,000
No matter what, kuma.

427
00:22:16,250 --> 00:22:18,875
[whimpering]

428
00:22:18,958 --> 00:22:20,708
[crowd yelling]

429
00:22:20,791 --> 00:22:30,750
♪

430
00:24:03,208 --> 00:24:06,125
[KYRIE] It's so...
incredibly hot...!

431
00:24:06,208 --> 00:24:08,375
We finally arrive on
the summer continent.

432
00:24:08,458 --> 00:24:10,916
Unable to make much ground
in the sweltering heat,

433
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:14,208
we take shelter in a village
run by a kind, old elephant.

434
00:24:14,291 --> 00:24:15,916
A village where
humans and beastmen

435
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:17,416
live together in harmony.

436
00:24:17,500 --> 00:24:20,416
A place where children can
run freely to laugh and play.

437
00:24:20,500 --> 00:24:22,666
Have we really
found a desert utopia?

438
00:24:22,750 --> 00:24:24,708
Next time on Sands
of Destruction,

439
00:24:24,791 --> 00:24:26,291
"There Are Two
Kinds of Summers."

440
00:24:26,375 --> 00:24:28,458
[MORTE] Toppy, you're
sweating like crazy!

441
00:24:28,541 --> 00:24:31,916
[TOPPY] Well it's not like
I can take off my coat, kuma!

